<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 315px 269px 0px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Asset Lifecycle Milestones for Information Delivery</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p class="p1" data-pasted="true">Not all information is needed at the same time or for the same reason. In this section, we define the Delivery milestone that drive the need for asset-related information throughout the asset lifecycle.</p>
<p class="p1">These Milestone help us clarify:</p>
<ul>
<li><p class="p1">When we expect certain data to be delivered</p></li>
<li><p class="p1">What that data is used for</p></li>
<li><p class="p1">How it supports our long-term asset management goals</p></li>
</ul>
<p data-pasted="true">ISO 19650 encourages appointing parties to define when information is needed in addition to what is needed.</p>
<p>Reference: ISO 19650-2, Clause 5.2.1 and 5.3.2 (Exchange Information Requirements and Delivery Milestones)</p>
<table data-pasted="true">
<thead><tr>
<th style="background-color: rgb(14, 30, 61);"><p class="p1"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Information Delivery Milestone</span></p></th>
<th style="background-color: rgb(14, 30, 61);"><p class="p1"><strong><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">What We Need</span></strong></p></th>
<th style="background-color: rgb(14, 30, 61);"><p class="p1"><strong><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Why It Matters</span></strong></p></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><p class="p1"><strong>Design Stage</strong></p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Expected performance, space requirements, standards</p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Supports early decision-making, space planning, and regulatory approval</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p class="p1"><strong>Procurement</strong></p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Model number, datasheets, lead times</p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Ensures compatibility, delivery, and installation coordination</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p class="p1"><strong>Installation</strong></p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Serial numbers, install date, installer name</p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Builds the foundation for commissioning and warranty tracking</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p class="p1"><strong>Commissioning</strong></p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Test results, commissioning date, certificates</p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Validates performance, prepares for handover</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p class="p1"><strong>Handover</strong></p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Full asset register, maintenance schedules, warranties</p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Transfers responsibility to FM/operations team</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p class="p1"><strong>Operation</strong></p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Maintenance logs, inspection records, replacement history</p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Supports long-term planning, compliance, and audits</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p class="p1"><strong>Replacement or Decommissioning</strong></p></td>
<td><p class="p1">End-of-life data, replacement options</p></td>
<td><p class="p1">Aids capital planning and sustainability tracking</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
